    "body": "So bots can start doing task at that point. (spawn is not the right event for this)",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "body": "Currently, bot.on('spawn') is the closest thing to this and even it is horrible... the first time it's used after connecting you need to wait 500ms because the protocol says you're spawned before you actually are, and various other things take even more time to load. Waiting 4 seconds works, but slows down testing and could be unnecessarily long. If you respawn from dieing, those 4 seconds are more or less wasted time.",
